  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A cornerstone of UNEP-DHI Centre&#x2019;s work is its direct supports UNEP&#x2019;s role in advancing
SDG 6 through its work in official global monitoring and reporting on the status of water
management, through a bespoke IWRM support programme in partnership with the
Global Water Partnership and UNDP Cap-Net, and through the development and
implementation of SDG 6 oriented projects. Water is a human right, critical for
livelihoods, food production, and sustainable development. Water is generated by
ecosystems and climate changes are manifested through drought and extreme floods.
Changes in water availability and variability can induce migration and ignite civil conflict.
UNEP-DHI Centre support UNEP in providing climate adaptation assistance to countries</narrative>
  </description>
